==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dent
<hw>Dent</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A variant of
<er>Dint</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stroke; a blow.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧That <xex>dent</xex> of thunder.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slight depression, or small notch or hollow, made
by a blow or by pressure; an indentation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A blow that would have made a <qex>dent</qex> in a pound of
butter.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dent
<hw>Dent</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Dented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Denting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make a dent upon; to
indent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The houses <qex>dented</qex> with bullets.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Dent
<hw>Dent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L. <ets>dens</ets>,
<ets>dentis</ets>, tooth. See <er>Tooth</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<def>A tooth, as of a card, a gear wheel, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dental</ent>⟦br⟧
